A major issue when considering the dynamics of gravitational systems such as dark matter halos, elliptical galaxies or star clusters in the non collisional regime is to understand the main processes underlying the creation of the quasi-stationary states that build up after a number of dynamical times, for instance the universal profiles of dark matter halos \citep{NFW1,NFW2}. 

